## Decisions Made
- Reject unknown WI IDs and cross-gate conflicts as separate errors (`work_items_not_found` exit 3, `wi_already_blocked_by_other_gate` exit 2) so the orchestrator can distinguish typo from contention.
- Place validation immediately after reading wi_store and before constructing the gate header so no partial state is written when the rejection fires.

## Problems Encountered
- None — the gate file uses a simple index map for lookup; validation slots in naturally.

## Constraints Identified
- `cmd_open` is the sole writer that opens gates; this validation does not need to be repeated in `cmd_resolve` (which works on already-validated state).
- The `blocked_by_gate` check excludes self-references (`== hdr_id`) so re-opening the same gate ID is not considered a conflict, matching the existing idempotency expectations.

